{
  "stem": "23090.6",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And he was granted, I heard, as high as President Truman, that the order was given that we may come here with the troops, with the first-- the transport of troops.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I, in fact, did come here with the GI's coming home.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And we embarked--",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In 1946.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 6 SECONDS] About May, June of 1946.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We were placed in a reception center in the Bronx.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the Jewish community came out and just wonderful, and they took us to Coney Island, to the Empire State Building.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And they were bring us foods.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And we were like-- we were like something out of-- out of another planet because-- not the fact that we were the youngest survivors, but the fact that we survived and the issue was so new.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And they were just wonderful to us.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And everybody wanted us to-- they would take us in as foster kids and so on.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But that was not the program.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "The program was to interview us and to rehab us as to-- first, we needed to know if our parents were still alive, before you went to foster homes and adoptions.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And I was interviewed by a social worker.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And I said I wanted to be a musician like my dad was.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And some guys wanted to be whatever their dads were.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And so they put out the word or whatever method they used, and there was a lady in Cleveland, Ohio, her name was Winifred Fryer, very wonderful, prominent human being, who was very cultured, and she was the president of the Cleveland Music School Settlement and the institute.",
      "word_count": 48
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And she said she would take a couple of boys into her home as foster boys, foster sons, and would avail us the education process and the musical background.",
      "word_count": 29
    }
  ],
